            , at the Yorkshire Grey, by the Watchhouse in Holborn, depos'd, That the Prisoner was a <rs id="t17221010-29-deflabel152" type="occupation">Taylor</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17221010-29-defend201 t17221010-29-deflabel152"></join> by Trade, and us'd to deal in Cloaths, and he never knew any harm by him; but being cross examin'd, confest that he had a very bad Name, and was reputed to be a Buyer of Stolen Goods. 
